73
00:09:04,710 --> 00:09:05,710
[GROANS]

74
00:09:05,790 --> 00:09:10,080
You mustn't tire yourself. You've gotta rest.

75
00:09:10,550 --> 00:09:12,460
You almost died.

76
00:09:24,180 --> 00:09:25,770
Open wide.

77
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:34,570
Your legs just sing grand opera when you move, don't they?

78
00:09:35,740 --> 00:09:39,140
It's not gonna hurt forever, Paul, I promise you.

79
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,780
Will I be able to walk?

80
00:09:41,870 --> 00:09:42,950
Of course you will.

81
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:45,580
And your arm will be fine, too.

82
00:09:45,660 --> 00:09:47,920
Your shoulder was pretty badly dislocated.

83
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,210
It was a little stubborn, but I finally popped it back in.

84
00:09:51,290 --> 00:09:54,130
What I'm most proud of is the work I did on those legs.

85
00:09:54,210 --> 00:09:55,710
Considering what I had around the house,

86
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:58,800
I don't think there's a doctor who could've done any better.

87
00:10:02,850 --> 00:10:05,140
It's not nearly as bad as it looks.

88
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:08,520
