204
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,120
Then he pays up and he's out the door.

205
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:05,500
No long-distance phone calls or Federal Express packages?

206
00:16:05,590 --> 00:16:07,790
Anything out of the ordinary?

207
00:16:08,250 --> 00:16:09,800
I don't think Mr. Sheldon likes

208
00:16:09,880 --> 00:16:12,340
for things to be out of the ordinary.

209
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:16,130
Considering who he is and all, famous and all,

210
00:16:16,140 --> 00:16:18,970
he doesn't put on airs.

211
00:16:18,970 --> 00:16:24,310
Drives up from New York in the same car each time, a '65 Mustang.

212
00:16:24,400 --> 00:16:26,400
He says it helps him to think.

213
00:16:27,610 --> 00:16:29,270
He's always been a good guest.

214
00:16:29,360 --> 00:16:32,030
Never makes a noise, never bothers a soul.

215
00:16:32,740 --> 00:16:34,700
I sure hope nothing's happened to him.

216
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:35,990
So do I.

217
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:40,200
I bet that old Mustang is pulling into New York right now.

218
00:16:41,290 --> 00:16:43,580
I'm sure you're right. Thanks, Libby.

219
00:16:43,670 --> 00:16:45,530
My pleasure.

220
00:16:58,930 --> 00:17:02,640
I know I'm only 40 pages into your book, but...

221
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:06,440
But what?
銀
222
00:17:07,650 --> 00:17:10,070
Nothing.

223
00:17:10,150 --> 00:17:12,400
